A4.text: Hawaii was admitted as a U.S. state on August 21, 1959.

A5.text: Alaska was admitted as the 49th state of the U.S. on January 3, 1959.

A6.text: Arizona became a U.S. state on February 14, 1912, coinciding with Valentine's Day.

A7.text: Arizona was the 48th state admitted to the U.S. and the last of the contiguous states to be admitted.

A8.text: New Mexico was admitted to the Union as the 47th state on January 6, 1912.
